<title>JAPAN: Softbank, Takefuji climb on speculative buying.</title>
<headline>Softbank, Takefuji climb on speculative buying.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares with high liquidity on the over-the-counter(OTC) market such as Softbank Corp and Takefuji Corp climbed in Friday morning trade as investors bought the shares in hopes of fast profits, brokers said.</p>
<p>As of 0100 GMT, Softbank stood at 7,850 yen, up from 7,600 at the Thursday close. Takefuji added 140 yen to 5,140 and Hikari Tsushin Inc rose 300 yen to 7,000. Shohkoh Fund and Co Ltd gained 400 yen to 27,800.  </p>
<p>The OTC index has lost about eight percent of its worth so far this month and brokers said that it was now at a good level to buy, in order to sell on the rebound. But they added that there was no serious bargain-hunting interest yet.</p>
